<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Kenobe on 06-01-2002 03:34 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">"There was absolutely NO, zero, nada, zippo, bottlenecks."

Going from Cleic main, to Rogue main about a year ago, Ive done both quests.

There are lots of areas where the rogue epic has bottle necks.  The fact that you either got lucky, or had some connections, doesnt mean that the rest of the rogues in the world had an easy time at it.

PP'ing the notes takes the time to raise the skill, and if you get caught and die you need to talk a friend into resing you in 3rd gate. Yeah if you have a cleric on second acct then no problem for you.  

The book in hate is fun and tricky to get solo. But if you go up and clear the first floor with your guild, then walk over and loot the book, then no biggie for you.

The bottle neck for me and many rogues is the KK robe.  Killed Phinny about 20 times, and the DE's in kith about a dozen, before I got mine.  This is more the norm, then getting to robe on first kill or the quill off the general.

As for the cleric epic, the only hard part now is waiting for Rage, and yes they need to fix that. The rest isn't hard to do at all.

I know all about the fustrations of being a cleric and doing its epic, however the grass isnt more green on anyones side.  The cleric epic is 100 times more powerful than Ragebringer. People know that and will fall over themselves helping clerics get it.  So in a debate of effort vs reward, one could hold a strong argument that the effort to get the cleric and rogue epic, is equal to the rewards they produce.




------------------
Kenobe Wan
Healer of the 56th Circle
Praxium Knight
Cazic-Thule

"And one time, at cleric camp, I...."</TEXTAREA>
